## Vendored browser libraries

The following minified libraries are vendored in
`services/openagentic-ui/public/artifact-runtime/` and are loaded by the
sandboxed artifact runtime. Each is distributed under its own license:

| File | Library | License | Project |
|---|---|---|---|
| react.production.min.js | React | MIT | https://github.com/facebook/react |
| react-dom.production.min.js | React DOM | MIT | https://github.com/facebook/react |
| babel.min.js | Babel (standalone) | MIT | https://github.com/babel/babel |
| chart.min.js | Chart.js | MIT | https://github.com/chartjs/Chart.js |
| d3.min.js | D3 | ISC | https://github.com/d3/d3 |
| d3-sankey.min.js | d3-sankey | MIT | https://github.com/d3/d3-sankey |
| katex.min.js | KaTeX | MIT | https://github.com/KaTeX/KaTeX |
| mermaid.min.js | Mermaid | MIT | https://github.com/mermaid-js/mermaid |
| plotly-basic.min.js | Plotly.js | MIT | https://github.com/plotly/plotly.js |

The full MIT License text (which governs the majority of the libraries above)
is reproduced at the end of this file; ISC is functionally equivalent. License
texts are also available in each project's repository linked above.

## Runtime dependencies

All other third-party dependencies are resolved from their package registries
(npm, PyPI, Go modules) at build time and are governed by the licenses declared
in each service's `package.json` / `requirements.txt` / `go.mod`. A scan of the
dependency tree found no AGPL/SSPL/BUSL/Commons-Clause or other
Apache-2.0-incompatible licenses.

